To solve this, we first condense the product as follows:For $x,y\in\mathbb{R}^+$,note \begin{align*}
\left(x+\frac1y\right)\left(x+\frac1y-2018\right)=-2018x-\frac{2018}{y}+x^2+\frac1{y^2}=-2018\left(x+\frac1y\right)+x^2+\frac1{y^2}.
\end{align*}Using the Arithmetic Mean-Geometric Mean (AM-GM) inequality on $x^2+\dfrac1{y^2}+2$ and setting $x^2=\dfrac1{y^2}$, we have \begin{align*}x^2+\frac1{y^2}+1\ge 2\left( x^2\cdot\frac1{y^2}\right)^{\frac12}\end{align*}with equality iff $x^2=\dfrac1{y^2}\implies x=y$; the minimum is then achieved at this ratio. Substituting everything into the original expression gives \begin{align*}&\left(x+\frac1y\right)\left(x+\frac1y-2018\right)+\left(y+\frac1x\right)\left(y+\frac1x-2018\right)\\ \ =&-2018\left(x+\frac1y\right)+x^2+\frac1{y^2}+1-2018\left(x+\frac1y\right)+1\\ \ =&-2(2018\left(x+\frac1y)=5072-2(2018\left(x+\frac1x)\\ \ =&5072-8072\sqrt2\end{align*}with $x=y$ and $\displaystyle\left(x+\frac1y\right)=\sqrt2$. We therefore attain $\boxed{5072-8072\sqrt2}$.\end{think} <answer>$5072-8072\sqrt2$</answer>

